The '''Bougainville bush warbler''' or '''odedi''' ('''''Horornis haddeni''''') is a [[bird]] [[species]] initially placed in the "[[Old World warbler]]" assemblage, but nowadays moved with its [[Conspecificity|congener]]s to the new cettiid warbler [[Family (taxonomy)|family]].

It was described as [[Bird species new to science|new to science]] in 2006. This bird is only known from the [[Crown Prince Range]] on [[Bougainville Island]] in the [[Solomon Islands]], [[Papua New Guinea]].<ref>{{cite journal |author=Mary LeCroy |author2=F. Keith Barker |name-list-style=amp|year=2006 |title=A new species of bush-warbler from Bougainville Island and a monophyletic origin for southwest Pacific ''Cettia'' |journal=[[American Museum Novitates]] |issue=3511 |pages=1–20 |url=http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/dspace/bitstream/2246/5786/1/N3511.pdf |doi=10.1206/0003-0082(2006)3511[1:ansobf]2.0.co;2|s2cid=59323110 }}</ref>

Its status was first evaluated for the [[IUCN Red List]] in 2008, being listed as [[near threatened]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[BirdLife International]] |year=2008 |url=http://www.birdlife.org/action/science/species/global_species_programme/whats_new.html |title=2008 IUCN Redlist status changes |access-date=May 23, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080914020126/http://www.birdlife.org/action/science/species/global_species_programme/whats_new.html |archive-date=September 14, 2008 }}</ref><ref name="iucn status 19 November 2021" />

